cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use HLER Scholar Reach in your research communication workflow, please cite it as below."
title: "HLER Scholar Reach: a human-in-the-loop skill for evidence-grounded, bilingual communication of academic papers and open-source research tools"
type: software
version: 0.2.0
date-released: "2026-07-04"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/maxwell2732/hler-scholar-reach"
authors:
  - family-names: "Zhu"
    given-names: "Chen"
    alias: "朱晨"
    affiliation: "遗传社科研究 (Genetic Social Science Research)"
keywords:
  - science communication
  - human-in-the-loop
  - research dissemination
  - claude-code-skill
  - academic integrity
  - bilingual
abstract: >-
  HLER Scholar Reach (v0.2, early-stage prototype) converts academic
  papers, working papers, research reports, and open-source research
  tools into reusable, audience-adapted bilingual (Chinese/English)
  communication packages, while preserving scientific conclusions,
  evidence boundaries, authorship, publication norms, and academic
  integrity. AI prepares; humans approve and publish.
